From a492692900680ef362dca0ec4120c94ca28fdcd5 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Vignesh C <vignc@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Sun, 9 Mar 2025 16:07:52 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] UPSTREAM:CP wifi:ath12k Decrement ahsta->num_peer during link
 sta unassignment

There is a gap in the logical_link_idx sent in the peer_assoc command.
For a two-link association, it should be 0 and 1. However, due to a
failure in creating link station (which was assigned link_idx 1) caused
by an AST failure, the next link creation is assigned link_idx 2.
This count should be decremented whenever a link station creation fails.

As a result, potential incorrect IPC messages are sent across the chipset
on FW, leading to unexpected behavior.

Decrement ahsta->num_peer which is assigned as link station logical_link_idx
during ath12k_mac_free_unassign_link_sta().

Patch-dependency: None
Patch-work: None

Signed-off-by: Vignesh C <vignc@qti.qualcomm.com>
---
 drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/mac.c | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

--- a/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/mac.c
+++ b/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/mac.c
@@ -10101,6 +10101,7 @@ static void ath12k_mac_free_unassign_lin
 
 	ahsta->links_map &= ~BIT(link_id);
 	ahsta->device_bitmap &= ~BIT(ab->wsi_info.index);
+	ahsta->num_peer--;
 	rcu_assign_pointer(ahsta->link[link_id], NULL);
 	synchronize_rcu();
 
